'''《查拉圖斯特拉如是說》，作品30'''（{{Lang-de|''Also sprach Zarathustra''}}<ref><!-- 该脚注不是参考资料，需要翻译 -->Listed in the closing credits of ''[[2001:_A_Space_Odyssey_(film)|2001: A Space Odyssey]]'' as "Thus ''spoke'' Zarathustra" but on the official soundtrack albums as "Thus ''[[Wikt:spake#verb|spake]]'' Zarathustra". The book by Nietzsche has been translated both ways and the title of Strauss's music is usually rendered in the original German whenever not discussed in the context of ''2001''. Although Britannica Online's entry lists the piece as "Thus ''spoke'' Zarathustra", music encyclopedias usually use "spake".</ref>）為[[理查·史特勞斯|理查·史特勞斯]]於1896年創作的一部[[交響詩|交響詩]]，其靈感來自於[[弗里德里希·尼采|弗里德里希·尼采]]的[[查拉圖斯特拉如是說|同名哲學小說]]<ref name="OAS49">[http://www.oldandsold.com/articles06/sy49.shtml "Richard Strauss – Tone-Poem, Death and Transfiguration, Opus 24"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080415043330/http://www.oldandsold.com/articles06/sy49.shtml |date=2008-04-15 }} (and other works), Old And Sold</ref>。1896年11月27日，該曲於法蘭克福首演；通常的演奏時間為约半個小時。

該作品在1896年首演之後，成為古典音樂中的經典曲目。其開頭的[[開場小號|開場小號]]——史特勞斯的註解中題名為{{單雙書名號轉換|日出}}（{{lang|en|Sunrise}}）<ref>[http://www.laphil.com/philpedia/piece-detail.cfm?id=673 ''Also sprach Zarathustra''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713184027/http://www.laphil.com/philpedia/piece-detail.cfm?id=673|date=2011-07-13}} – notes by [[Los_Angeles_Philharmonic|Los Angeles Philharmonic]]</ref>——在1968年[[史丹利·庫柏力克|-{zh-hans:斯坦利·库布里克;zh-hk:史丹利·寇比力克;zh-tw:史丹利·庫柏力克;}-]]採用於電影《[[2001太空漫遊_(電影)|2001太空漫遊]]》後，成為家喻戶曉的名曲<ref>[http://www.bsomusic.org/main.taf?p=1,9,3,1,1,3&PerfNo=9863 Also Sprach Zarathustra!] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bsomusic.org/main.taf?p=1,9,3,1,1,3&PerfNo=9863 |date=20131004214645 }} Baltimore Symphony Orchestra, January 2012.</ref>。

